'derivation': The application object defines a relationship where the  related  is derived from the  relating ;
A raster image may be derived from a three-dimensional CAD model.

				A html version may be derived from a text document as an alternative.

'reference': The application object defines a relationship where the  related document is referenced from the  
			relating;
A hyperlink is an example for a 'reference'.

'substitution': The application object defines a relationship where the  related

		 replaces the  relating 
